               </dateline><salute>Mr. Walt Whitman</salute>  
            </opener>
            
            <p>I have just been to Mr Alvord's and find your Drum taps printed very nicely indeed<!--The previous sentence has been inserted to replace "just <gap reason="illegible"/>Ahrend's and find <gap reason="illegible"/> Taps pri<gap reason="illegible"/>nicely indeed." The Miller annotation and Ted's article list the printer's name as 'Alvord' not  Ahrend; also, Ted provides a reading of the entire sentence which I transcribe above. I have also changed 'Ahrend' to 'Alvord' below.-->.  Please send me <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#vys" cert="low">balance</unclear> of bill ($94.25) as per agreement and I will deliver them to your binder.  The copy of "Leaves of Grass" is at my office subject to your order.  The plates of "Drum Taps" are in Mr. Alvord's vault.</p>
            <closer rend="right">
               <salute>Respectfully,</salute>
               <signed>P. Eckler</signed>
               <dateline>40 Fulton St.</dateline>
            </closer>
         
      </body>
